notes:
Combined Statistical Areas (CSAs) are defined by the Office of Management and Budget (OMB) and
               consist of two or more adjacent Core Based Statistical Areas (CBSAs) that have significant employment interchanges. The CBSAs that combine to create a
               CSA retain separate identities within the larger CSA. Because CSAs represent groupings of CBSAs, they should not be ranked or compared with individual
               CBSAs. The CSA boundaries are those defined by OMB based on the 2010 Census and published in 2013.
